Portfolio Manager

Overview

The Portfolio Manager is the central intelligence layer of the AI Treasury Agent.

It aggregates wallet balances, market data, treasury policies, and risk assessments to produce portfolio insights and actionable recommendations. Rather than executing transactions directly, it evaluates the current treasury state and proposes optimized strategies aligned with the organization's objectives.

The Portfolio Manager serves as the decision engine that connects all other system components.



Objectives

The Portfolio Manager aims to:

Maintain an up-to-date view of the treasury
Calculate portfolio allocation
Monitor asset performance
Optimize capital allocation
Recommend portfolio rebalancing
Enforce treasury policies
Generate AI-powered recommendations
Support governance and executive reporting
Core Responsibilities
Portfolio Aggregation

The Portfolio Manager consolidates data from all monitored wallets into a unified treasury view.

It calculates:

Total portfolio value
Asset allocation
Chain allocation
Wallet allocation
Stablecoin exposure
Yield-generating positions
Allocation Analysis

The module continuously evaluates portfolio composition.

Example allocation:

Asset	Allocation
ETH	42%
USDC	28%
BTC	18%
TAIKO	7%
Other	5%

The Portfolio Manager compares current allocation against predefined treasury policies.

Performance Tracking

The system monitors treasury performance over time.

Metrics include:

Total portfolio value
Daily return
Weekly return
Monthly return
Unrealized gains
Realized gains
Asset performance
Portfolio growth

Example:

{
  "portfolio_value_usd": 2850000,
  "daily_return": 1.2,
  "monthly_return": 8.4,
  "best_performing_asset": "ETH"
}
Rebalancing Analysis

The Portfolio Manager evaluates whether portfolio allocations remain within acceptable policy limits.

Example conditions:

ETH allocation exceeds maximum target
Stablecoin allocation below minimum reserve
Single protocol exposure too high
Chain concentration exceeds policy

Example recommendation:

{
  "action": "rebalance",
  "reason": "ETH allocation exceeds target by 12%",
  "priority": "high"
}
Treasury Policies

The module validates portfolio composition against configurable treasury policies.

Examples:

Maximum allocation per asset
Minimum stablecoin reserves
Maximum protocol exposure
Maximum chain exposure
Minimum liquidity requirements
Approved investment universe

Example:

{
  "max_asset_allocation": 40,
  "min_stablecoin_reserve": 20,
  "max_protocol_exposure": 25
}
AI Recommendation Engine

The AI recommendation engine combines portfolio analytics with market conditions and risk assessments.

Possible recommendations include:

Increase stablecoin reserves
Reduce exposure to volatile assets
Diversify across chains
Rebalance allocations
Allocate idle capital to yield opportunities
Reduce protocol concentration
Delay execution due to unfavorable market conditions

Example:

{
  "summary": "Portfolio concentration exceeds treasury policy.",
  "recommendation": "Reduce ETH allocation and increase USDC reserves.",
  "confidence": 0.94
}
